      {"name": "salt", "quantity": null, "unit": "pinch"},
      {"name": "raspberry jam", "quantity": null, "unit": "q.b."}
    ],
    "instructions": "mix 400g of room temp. (fatty and not grainy) curd with butter, sugar, vanilla powder and salt. mix baking powder in the flour and then sift it into the curd mass - knead until it is well incorporated. squish the dough into a pancake, wrap and place into the frige (let it rest for 1-2 hours). make the filling by mixing 300g curd, 50g sugar and vanilla powder. depending on your preferece you can either mix it jam now, add drops to each pocker or just leave as is. place chilled dough on a well floured surface and roll it out to 4-5mm in thickness. cut out 10cm circles and place in a tsp on filling. fold in half and press the edges together. rest all pocker in the fridge for about 15 minutes and then immediately place in a preheated oven at 190C for 20-25 minutes. let it cool and decorate with powdered sugar if you like. these pockets can be freezed for 3-6 months.",
    "cookTime": "1 hour",
    "servings": 20,
    "tags": ["dessert", "latvian", "curd"],
    "image": "/images/cranberry-jam.jpg"
  },
